HEADWORD: Pair production
<hw>Pair" pro*duc"tion</hw> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The simultaneous
creation of a particle and its antiparticle, such as an electron and
positron, from a photon; -- usually due to its interaction with the
strong field near a nucleus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

